<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="484" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1084,1397]" box="[199,1179,1119,1144]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,1017,1119,1144]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">Recorded damage and economic importance in the orchards of Iran:</emphasis>
Not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1084,1397]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,939,1156,1181]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
A potential vector for 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1338,1156,1181]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Xanthomonadaceae" genus="Xylella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Xanthomonadales" pageId="9" pageNumber="484" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="fastidiosa">
<emphasis box="[1198,1338,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">X. fastidiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and elm yellows phytoplasma. The species also tested positive for Aster yellows in vineyards in Czech Republic (
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="484" refId="ref18622" refString="Delong, D. M. &amp; Severin, H. H. P. (1950) Spittle- insect vectors of pierce's disease virus. Hilgardia, 19 (11), 339 - 356. https: // doi. org / 10.3733 / hilg. v 19 n 11 p 339" type="journal article">DeLong &amp; Severin 1950</bibRefCitation>
; EFSA 2013; 
<bibRefCitation box="[489,724,1228,1253]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484" refId="ref21229" refString="Orsagova, H., Brezikova, M. &amp; Schlesingerova, G. (2011) Presence of phytoplasmas in hemipterans in Czech vineyards. Bulletin of Insectology, 64 (Supplement), 119 - 120." type="journal article">
Orsagova 
<emphasis box="[603,651,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[736,923,1228,1253]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484" refId="ref21747" refString="Rosa, C., Mc Carthy, E., Duong, K., Hoover, G. &amp; Moorman, G. (2014) First Report of the Spittlebug Lepyronia quadrangularis and the Leafhopper Latalus sp. as Vectors of the Elm Yellows Associated Phytoplasma, Candidatus Phytoplasma ulmi in North America. Plant Disease, 98 (1), 154. https: // doi. org / 10.1094 / PDIS- 06 - 13 - 0628 - PDN" type="journal article">
Rosa 
<emphasis box="[799,848,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1084,1397]" box="[199,1342,1263,1288]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,1263,1288]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">Recorded distribution in Iran:</emphasis>
Norh, northwest, southwest and south (
<bibRefCitation box="[1006,1330,1263,1288]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484" refId="ref20791" refString="Mozaffarian, F. &amp; Wilson, M. R. (2015) The aphrophorid spittlebugs of Iran (Hemiptera: Cercopoidea: Aphrophoridae). Zootaxa, 4052 (4), 442 - 456. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4052.4.2" type="journal article">Mozaffarian &amp; Wilson 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1084,1397]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,1300,1325]" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">Conclusion:</emphasis>
Although the species has not been recorded as a pest in Iranian orchards, the ability of the species to transmit diseases needs to be investigated due to the records in other parts of the world and its wide distribution in Iran.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
